value.title: Ingraham: Democrats hiding 'true agenda' from middle, working class by trotting out Biden cliches
value.excerpt: President Trump, not Joe Biden, is the candidate who truly fights for the working class, Laura Ingraham argued Wednesday on "The Ingraham Angle."

value.title: Hunter Biden: Here's what he has said about his Burisma role in Ukraine
value.excerpt: The son of former Vice President Joe Biden has mostly remained mum on the allegations of impropriety while working on the board of Ukrainian oil company Burisma. Here’s what he has said about it in the past.

value.title: Jennifer Lawrence says Trump altered her political views: ‘There’s been a line drawn in the sand’
value.excerpt: Jennifer Lawrence said despite the fact she grew up in a Republican household, because of Trump, she has become more open-minded about politics "based on the things I learned."

value.title: Trump envoy Richard Grenell met with Venezuelan politician in bid to oust Maduro: report
value.excerpt: Richard Grenell, the Trump administration's special envoy for Serbia and Kosovo Peace Negotiations, reportedly tried in September to negotiate with a Venezuelan politician close to the country's strongman president, Nicolas Maduro, in order to obtain the controversial leader's peaceful exit from office.

value.title: Trump grants clemency to Alice Marie Johnson associate, 4 other nonviolent criminals
value.excerpt: President Trump granted clemency on Wednesday to five prisoners-- including one who was an associate of Alice Marie Johnson-- who were each serving time in prison for non-violent offenses.

value.title: Blackburn: Trump should focus on his 'incredible record' at presidential debate, not 'Biden Inc.'
value.excerpt: President Trump should focus on his own accomplishments during Thursday night's second and final presidential debate against Joe Biden, Sen. Marsha Blackburn, R-Tenn., told "Special Report" Wednesday.

value.title: Trump campaign, Nevada GOP threaten to sue Clark County over attempts to ‘obstruct’ election observation
value.excerpt: The campaign and state Republicans claim that observers have been banned from certain areas where ballots are handled.

value.title: Chronicled: Who is Kamala Harris? New podcast by The Chronicle coming soon
value.excerpt: Is Kamala Harris a cop or progressive? A Berkeley radical or Beltway insider? This six-part podcast series from the San Francisco Chronicle delves into the making of a candidate. Listen to the trailer and subscribe on Apple,

value.title: Biden drops LA Mayor Eric Garcetti from event after two more men accuse close adviser of sexual misconduct
value.excerpt: Los Angeles Mayor Eric Garcetti’s chances for a cabinet post in a Biden administration are increasingly in doubt now that two more men have accused Garcetti’s close adviser of sexual misconduct.

value.title: CNN Polls: Biden leads in Pennsylvania and tight race remains in Florida
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Joe Biden holds a lead in Pennsylvania and neither he nor President Donald Trump leads in the critical state of Florida, according to new CNN polls conducted by SSRS.

value.title: Trump administration continues to send mixed messages about future of US troops in Afghanistan
value.excerpt: The Trump administration continued to send contradictory messages about the future of US troops in Afghanistan on Wednesday.

value.title: Inside Melania Trump's unprecedented campaign trail absence
value.excerpt: First lady Melania Trump -- in a historic break from precedent -- has yet to set foot on the campaign trail this year even as her husband, President Donald Trump, fights for votes, especially among suburban White women with whom she could hold appeal.

value.title: Biden endorses Texas Democratic House candidate Julie Oliver
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden has thrown his support behind progressive congressional candidate Julie Oliver in her race for a House seat in central Texas.

value.title: 'Panicked' Sen. Ron Johnson touts Trump to Wisconsin leaders
value.excerpt: A “panicked” Sen. Ron Johnson is urging members of the state chamber of commerce in battleground Wisconsin to vote for President Donald Trump

value.title: Maryland man charged with threatening Biden, Harris in letter on supporter's doorstep
value.excerpt: Federal prosecutors on Wednesday charged a Maryland man with threatening Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden and running mate Kamala Harris in a letter left on the doorstep of a someone with a yard sign supporting their campaign.

value.title: Does appearing at Trump rallies help Martha McSally in Arizona's US Senate race?
value.excerpt: Sen. Martha McSally was on hand at President Donald Trump's rallies in Prescott and Tucson. Does campaigning with Trump help her Senate candidacy?

value.title: Trump Wants to Cut Democrat Cities’ COVID Funding—During a Surge In Cases
value.excerpt: The proposed cuts come as apparent retribution for Democratic mayors not “dominating” their citizens protesting this summer.

value.title: Live at 1:30: VP Mike Pence visits Portsmouth for rally
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence will be in the Granite State on Wednesday for a campaign event. He is scheduled to speak to supporters at a rally in Portsmouth at 1:30 p.m. The event will be streamed live above this article on WMUR.

value.title: Lindsey Graham Says Joe Biden Is 'In His Basement' Because He 'Can't Carry a Message'
value.excerpt: "President Trump is ... going all over the country with a lot of energy. He has really accomplished a lot in his first time," said the Republican senator.

value.title: Barack Obama to hold his first in-person event for Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Former President Barack Obama is returning to Philadelphia for his first in-person 2020 campaign event for Joe Biden

value.title: FBI says it has ‘nothing to add’ to Ratcliffe’s remarks about Hunter Biden, Russian disinformation
value.excerpt: In a carefully worded letter to Congress two weeks before Election Day, the bureau tries to avoid its 2016 errors.

value.title: Pollster who predicted 2016 result says Trump on track to win again with help of 'hidden' support
value.excerpt: With two weeks left until Election Day, 35 million Americans having already voted, and most polls showing Joe Biden leading President Trump, Trafalgar Group chief pollster Robert Cahaly told “Hannity” Tuesday the incumbent is likely to be reelected.

value.title: Alleged China-Fighter Donald Trump Has Secret Chinese Bank Account
value.excerpt: Another big scandal — and huge conflict of interest — has surfaced from the tax returns obtained by the New York Times.

value.title: Joe Biden: Cameron Peak, CalWood fires are 'deadly signs' of climate change
value.excerpt: Joe Biden's statement on Northern Colorado's Cameron Peak fire was the first time a major party presidential candidate has name-checked the fire.

value.title: Tiffany Trump says her father 'has always supported' LGBTQ people
value.excerpt: "Prior to politics, he supported gays, lesbians, the LGBQIA+ community," she said of the president at a Trump Pride event in Florida.
